++
prefix variable
pre-increment
https://docs.raku.org/language/operators#prefix_++
Calls the C<.succ> method on the variable, stores it in the
variable and returns the result.

++⚛
prefix integer variable
atomic pre-increment by 1
https://docs.raku.org/type/atomicint#prefix_++⚛
Atomically increment the atomic integer variable and return its
value.

--
prefix variable
pre-decrement by 1
https://docs.raku.org/language/operators#prefix_--
Calls the C<.pred> method on the variable, stores it in the
variable and returns the result.

--⚛
prefix integer variable
atomic pre-decrement by 1
https://docs.raku.org/type/atomicint#prefix_--⚛
Atomically decrement the atomic integer variable and return its
value.

++
postfix variable
post-increment
https://docs.raku.org/language/operators#postfix_++
Keeps the value of the variable, calls the C<.succ> method on the
variable, stores it in the variable and returns the previously
saved result.

⚛++
postfix integer variable
atomic post-increment by 1
https://docs.raku.org/type/atomicint#postfix_⚛++
Keeps the value of the variable, then atomically increment the
atomic integer variable and return the previously saved value.

--
postfix variable
post-decrement
https://docs.raku.org/language/operators#postfix_--
Keeps the value of the variable, calls the C<.pred> method on the
variable, stores it in the variable and returns the previously
saved result.

⚛--
postfix integer variable
atomic post-decrement by 1
https://docs.raku.org/type/atomicint#postfix_⚛--
Keeps the value of the variable, then atomically decrement the
atomic integer variable and return the previously saved value.


contains the infix operators for incrementing / decrementing (usually)
numeric values.
